# Env Usage Guardrails

- Treat `config/env.ts`, `.agent/contracts/env.contract.json`, and `.planning/spec-kit/manifest/schemas/env.schema.json` as one unit.
- Any env variable add/remove/rename must update all three files in the same change.
- Keep defaults, ranges, and type checks explicit in `config/env.ts`.
- Keep schema constraints synchronized with runtime validation behavior.
- Never print or persist secret env values in logs, artifacts, docs, or tests.
- If env behavior changes, run `npm run lint` and `npm run test:integration`.

